  "prompt": "Are Australian aboriginals descendants from people from Africa that left over 75,000 years ago?",
  "response": "Yes, the Australian Aboriginal people are widely believed to be descendants of early humans who migrated out of Africa. Genetic and archaeological evidence suggests that their ancestors left Africa over 75,000 years ago and embarked on a lengthy journey, eventually arriving in Australia. This migration is part of a broader movement known as the \"Out of Africa\" theory, which posits that all modern humans can trace their origins back to Africa. These early settlers reached Australia via Southern Asia, likely navigating through Southeast Asia and eventually crossing the sea to find their new home. This remarkable migration represents one of the oldest continuous cultures in the world.",
